<title>USA: Banc One ends share repurchase plan.</title>
<headline>Banc One ends share repurchase plan.</headline>
<dateline>COLUMBUS, Ohio 1997-05-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Banc One Corp said on Wednesday that it has terminated its share repurchase authorization as the company prepares for its acquisition of First USA Inc.</p>
<p>Banc One scheduled a special shareholders meeting to vote on the deal on June 26, 1997, the bank said.  First USA scheduled its shareholder vote for the deal on June 27, Banc One said.  </p>
<p>Banc One had an April 1996 authorization to repurchase 10 million shares and a January 1997 authorization to repurchase up to 12 million shares.</p>
<p>Banc One said 9.5 million shares were repurchased under the April 1996 program, while 8.1 million shares were repurchased in the January 1997 program, which was associated with the acquisition of Liberty Bancorp Inc.</p>
